Trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed, no need to peel) then grate on the coarse side of your
#grater{}. Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Halve
the @lemon{1/2}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a
#garlic press{}). Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium heat (no oil). Once hot,
add the @cashew pieces{25} and dry-fry, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted,
~{1-2%minutes}. Then remove to a small #bowl{}.

> TIP: Watch cashews like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Pour the @water{300%ml}(cold, for the rice) into a medium #saucepan{} with a
tight-fitting #lid{}. Stir in the @basmati rice{150%g}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and half of
the @white cumin seeds{1/2}(for the rice). Cover with the lid and bring to the
boil on medium-high heat. Once boiling, turn the heat down to its lowest setting.
Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered)
and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice
will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in the (now empty) frying pan on medium-high heat.
Once hot, add the @diced chicken thigh{260%g} to the pan. Fry until browned,
~{3-4%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Then add the @sliced mushrooms{80%g} and
fry until they start to soften and turn golden, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling chicken and its packaging.

Once the chicken has browned and the mushrooms are golden, add the
@rogan josh curry paste{50%g} and garlic to the pan. Cook until fragrant,
~{30%seconds}, stirring continuously. Then add the @boscaiola sauce{1} and
@water{100%ml}(for the sauce), mixing well to combine. Bring to the boil, then
reduce the heat and simmer gently until the chicken is cooked and the sauce has
thickened slightly, ~{5-6%minutes}. When ready, remove from the heat. Taste and
season with @?salt{} and @?black pepper{} if needed.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

While the curry and the rice cooks, pop the grated carrot into a small bowl. Add
the coriander and remaining @white cumin seeds{1/2}(for the kachumber). Pour in
the @olive oil{1%tbsp}(for the dressing), squeeze in some lemon juice and season
with salt and pepper. Mix well to combine. Taste and add more lemon juice, salt
or pepper if needed. Leave your carrot kachumber aside for now.

When everything is ready, fluff up the cumin rice with a fork then divide it
between your #dishes{}. Spoon over the chicken and mushroom rogan josh and
garnish with the toasted cashews. Serve with the carrot kachumber on the side
and tuck in. Enjoy!